modules.description: Provides functions to trigger device vibrations with specified patterns and durations. Works with arrays of integers representing vibration intervals and single integer values for timeout periods. Used to implement custom vibration alerts in mobile applications.

Provides functions to trigger device vibration with a specified duration, play a custom vibration pattern using an array of intervals, and cancel ongoing vibrations. Works with integers and integer arrays to control vibration behavior. Used to implement haptic feedback in mobile applications, such as alerting users to events with specific vibration sequences.
